<br>
And that, my friend.. is exactly my point.  As long as everyone stays fair, I have seen reservation systems flourish.  But indeed, you are correct when you say that some do take advantage of the system... for that, they must live with the ridicule of their peers and the disrespect of their reservations.<br>
<br>
I am not trying to bash the power guilds.  In fact, most of them are incredibly sympathetic to our pleese.  However, there is always one that falls off the honor wagon.. and for that, their progress as a guild will do one of two things: 1) annoy all of their potential future recruits, or, 2) entice people to join them as they are the guild that sets the pace.  Why do they set the pace you ask, because there is absolutely nothing that we can do about it.<br>
<br>
=)<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
