<br>
I was originally from an uber crowded blue server with off-hours guilds (Asian and the like who are awake when we sleep).  And no mob was EVER up.<br>
<br>
The larger more competitive guilds abandoned the reservation system that the small guilds and pick-up raids used.<br>
<br>
This meant that when a raid was scheduled.. not only was there a 50% chance that the zone had been cleared by an off-time guild... as they never bothered checking any board, but then you had the larger guilds who would go up and clear JUST the minis in Hate, or the revenants.. or JUST the Shissar in Fear... leaving just the junk mobs behind.  Some being as rude as jumping a plane when we had already been fighting in it.<br>
<br>
We do not want to go here.<br>
<br>
Currently this is a nice undercrowed server.. but for bigger guilds to feel *inconvenienced* by checkin one board, it snobby and rude.<br>
<br>
As smaller guilds we do get constantly inconvienced by mob-ganking.  It is hard planning a raid three weeks in advance, and arriving to find another guild just cleared the plane to get to the mob boss.<br>
<br>
Personally.. I think the larger guilds should have to plan as well.. since smaller groups cannot kill gods, and such without wipeouts.. why not let them do the work.. and schedule you expedition after they have done what they have done.<br>
<br>
Only thinking you are better than your peers leads to the *inconvenience* idea of checking a board.<br>
<br>
I have never been a member of an uber guild.  I had a 62 cleric on another server who turned down 4 invites from several high teir guilds.. just to stay with friends.<br>
<br>
I pay the same $12 a month that you do.  How is your experience worth any more than mine is?<br>
